Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.72,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.20,0:01:49.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've waited for two years, and we\Nhaven't had the chance to talk yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.68,0:01:59.68,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 4\NTorogai's Letter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.41,0:03:03.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Stay a little longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.96,0:03:21.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, it was too far away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.93,0:03:28.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I waited for nearly a month.\NCouldn't the Water Folk hang on a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.81,0:03:34.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps proper communication\Nisn't possible unless I'm at the Knot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.18,0:03:44.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the second prince\Ndidn't die in that fire after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.22,0:03:49.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I wonder what he meant by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.10,0:03:53.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An egg?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.40,0:03:57.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, a being from Nayug laid an egg\Nhere in this world, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.57,0:04:04.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go to the Knot right away\Nand talk to the Water Folk again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.54,0:04:08.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I never dreamed a chance like this\Nwould present itself in my lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:12.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What I wouldn't give to see that egg\Nwith my own two eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.68,0:04:18.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But first of all, I suppose I should\Nget rid of those pesky pups!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.02,0:04:22.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.49,0:04:25.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't live with\Nmyself if I didn't give...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.66,0:04:29.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that cheeky brat of a\Nmaster star reader a piece of my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.23,0:04:33.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Come down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.61,0:04:44.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're a dour-looking\Npair of pups, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.33,0:05:39.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'd do well to remember this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.10,0:05:43.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The more beautiful the flower,\Nthe deadlier its fragrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.21,0:05:46.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They don't always send you off\Nto a pleasant sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.48,0:05:58.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You make sure that this message\Ngets delivered, you stupid pups.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.34,0:06:18.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is Shuga, who will be\Nserving Your Majesty in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.28,0:06:22.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He is rather young, is he not?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.21,0:06:27.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. He is the youngest\Nstar reader in history...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.68,0:06:31.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and until recently, was\Ntutor-governor of Ninomiya Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.12,0:06:34.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He is that talented, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:41.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga, in view of your talents,\Nyou may serve in my shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.06,0:06:44.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall redouble all of my efforts, Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.97,0:06:47.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what of the Hunters' pursuit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.67,0:06:51.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They have failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.97,0:06:53.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Failed, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.61,0:06:54.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.48,0:07:02.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is unprecedented.\NFailing to carry out my command...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.62,0:07:07.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was this female bodyguard\Ntruly that formidable?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.29,0:07:16.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or perhaps they were under\Nthe water demon's protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.13,0:07:18.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that may be the case, Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.20,0:07:22.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, while this woman\Nmay have driven the Hunters away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:25.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am told that she was\Ngravely injured in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.11,0:07:29.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That being the case, it is unlikely\Nthat she could have gone far.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.58,0:07:33.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Grant me leave to dispatch\Nthe remaining Hunters, and surely...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.65,0:07:38.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How many Hunters are still\Nable to perform their duties?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.85,0:07:41.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Including myself, there are five, Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.16,0:07:46.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, let us\Ntry another method.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.30,0:07:47.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sire?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.76,0:07:50.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as Chagum's\Nviewing ceremonies are completed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.73,0:07:53.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...conduct a manhunt\Nto appease his spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.44,0:07:55.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We shall dispatch troops\Nwho know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.50,0:07:59.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mobilize them under the pretext\Nof searching for the arsonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.08,0:08:03.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mon, that will be your cover\Nto operate in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.55,0:08:04.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Sire!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:28.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Preparations to place the body\Nin the coffin seem to be proceeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.01,0:08:33.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am told that Chagum's body\Nwas never found.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.11,0:08:36.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, they are still\Npreparing a coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.25,0:08:40.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is Chagum really dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.75,0:08:45.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Body or no body, the second prince\Nhas indeed passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.32,0:08:49.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then why has the second queen\Nbeen moved to the Inner Palace?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.19,0:08:54.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Chagum is indeed dead,\Nsurely that is cruel treatment!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.06,0:09:00.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One who will eventually\Nrule this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.10,0:09:03.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...ought not concern himself\Nwith such trivial matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.67,0:09:07.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it trivial to show concern for\Nthe mother of my younger brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.48,0:09:13.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then one must truly be\Ncold of heart to be mikado.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.42,0:09:21.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is for that reason that I wanted\NChagum to live in a world...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.66,0:09:24.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...devoid of such callousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.56,0:09:29.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Simply watching Chagum\Nrunning and playing happily...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.27,0:09:32.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...raised my spirits to no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.83,0:10:00.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Become empty vessels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.47,0:10:06.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.67,0:10:11.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have received an unusual letter\Nfrom the magic weaver.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.31,0:10:16.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely those who pursued the\Nmagic weaver did not fail me as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.88,0:10:21.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what is this letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.22,0:10:26.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.06,0:10:36.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.80,0:10:40.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mon, I don't intend to dwell on\Nwhat is over and done with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.44,0:10:44.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no shortage of matters that\Nyou and your men must attend to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.31,0:10:47.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, heal your wounds and\Nbe ready for your next orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.58,0:10:48.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.35,0:10:55.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Read it. It is addressed to you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.69,0:10:58.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To my dear star readers...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.99,0:11:02.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who, rather than gaze at the stars,\Ninstead fix their gaze on their feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.19,0:11:05.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ignoring the nature of the being\Nthat resides in the second prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.79,0:11:08.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...will result in a terrible\Ndrought afflicting this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.90,0:11:13.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your ancestors had the capacity\Nto work for a common cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.57,0:11:16.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Though it pains me to say so,\Nwe Yakoo have also...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.11,0:11:18.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...misplaced something vital\Nin the depths of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.71,0:11:23.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall now go forth to visit one\Nwho knows the truth of this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.31,0:11:27.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until I return, I suggest you refrain\Nfrom taking any rash action.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.69,0:11:32.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How do you interpret this letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.76,0:11:36.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai is already aware of\Nthe sign of the great drought...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.46,0:11:41.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and is about to undertake an\Ninvestigation to further study its cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:43.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is how I interpret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.57,0:11:49.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master, I believe we should work\Nwith the Yakoo magic weavers...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.97,0:11:52.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and conduct an exchange\Nof knowledge with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.01,0:11:54.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Exchange knowledge with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.48,0:12:00.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Reveal all to the magic Weavers?\NThe very thought is outrageous!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.62,0:12:05.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Star readers must never go to\Nmagic weavers in search of advice!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.22,0:12:06.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But they are more knowledgeable on...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.86,0:12:08.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But they are more knowledgeable on...\NDo not forget...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:13.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that the honor of Shin-Yogo\Nhangs in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.93,0:12:21.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, I do not suggest that\Nwe attempt to slay the prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.60,0:12:23.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and the water demon\Nthat possesses him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.91,0:12:27.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here in the Star Palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.48,0:12:31.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there is a storehouse which only\Nthe master star readers know of.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.35,0:12:36.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that room lie epistles left behind\Nby grand master star reader Nanai...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.15,0:12:39.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who played such a pivotal role\Nin the founding of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.96,0:12:43.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, being written in\Nthe ancient Yogo tongue...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.89,0:12:48.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...deciphering them all will take\Nconsiderable time and effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.06,0:12:53.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga, you are hereby relieved\Nof your duties as star reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.37,0:12:58.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To prevent the drought likely to befall\Nour country in the near future...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.64,0:13:01.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I charge you with the task\Nof deciphering the epistles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.74,0:13:04.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Decipher the epistles\Nand find a means...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.08,0:13:08.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...of vanquishing the water demon\Nbefore the magic weaver does.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.52,0:13:11.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A way to vanquish the water demon...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.06,0:13:16.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am honored to accept this task\Nof deciphering the epistles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.19,0:13:20.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Report to me everything\Nthat you uncover.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.86,0:13:22.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have every faith in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.00,0:13:34.01,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.69,0:13:52.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've managed to patch you up...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.15,0:14:14.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world\Nhappened to you, Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.35,0:14:19.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.50,0:14:32.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.70,0:14:37.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I can't do anything right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.64,0:14:41.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so hard on yourself.\NIt isn't your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.48,0:14:45.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's her own fault for\Nbeing so reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.78,0:14:51.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, going by what you've told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.55,0:14:55.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I suppose that would make this boy\Nthe prince of Ninomiya Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.56,0:14:59.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.67,0:15:13.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.24,0:15:16.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.45,0:15:25.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long have I been unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.79,0:15:27.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long have I been unconscious?\NIt hasn't even been a full day yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.82,0:15:29.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A day?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.29,0:15:37.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda, did you sense anyone\Naround where you found me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.67,0:15:41.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I saw there were your footprints\Nand drops of your blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.54,0:15:43.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.77,0:15:49.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard about your situation.\NYou should really thank these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.11,0:15:52.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Toya...thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:16:01.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda, did anything\Nhappen to the boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.29,0:16:06.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.80,0:16:10.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, is he really...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.90,0:16:15.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to get you involved in all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.27,0:16:21.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you've probably guessed,\Nhe's Shin-Yogo's second prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.41,0:16:25.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.51,0:16:28.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's been\Npossessed by a spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.08,0:16:31.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the Mikado considers him tainted\Nand has ordered him to be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.42,0:16:35.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why the second queen\Nhired me as his bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.96,0:16:37.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.56,0:16:39.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're really hopeless!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.20,0:16:46.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I want to help him\Nas much as the next person, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.24,0:16:51.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda, I want you to\Nfind out what that spirit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.74,0:16:55.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If possible, I'd like you to\Nremove it from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:57.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A spirit, you say? I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.98,0:17:00.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your master's the only one\Nwho can handle it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.55,0:17:02.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't say that I couldn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:10.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here, let me take a quick look.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.51,0:17:28.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.48,0:17:39.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling that\NI'm in over my head here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.66,0:17:40.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.29,0:17:44.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems to be something\Nthat came from Nayug.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.09,0:17:49.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning we'll need to have\NTorogai take a look, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.46,0:17:53.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but she's out drifting\Nwherever the wind takes her again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.24,0:17:54.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.41,0:17:58.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.81,0:18:01.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any food\Nthat will help me recover?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.78,0:18:03.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time to spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.05,0:18:06.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long will it take\Nthis wound to heal?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.72,0:18:10.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous.\NIt'll take even you ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.05,0:18:12.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seven if we're being optimistic...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:14.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait that long.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.26,0:18:16.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They might be at\Nour throats any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.79,0:18:18.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.73,0:18:22.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't bear to cause you\Nany more trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.43,0:18:25.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When did we say anything\Nabout you troubling us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.27,0:18:29.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll feed you properly.\NAnd I'll protect you from your pursuers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.30,0:18:31.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So stop worrying and\Nfocus on getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.47,0:18:33.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.15,0:18:41.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry.\NGo ahead and sleep too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.53,0:18:59.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This time of year, there are plenty of\Nherbs that are good for wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.07,0:19:04.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This old lady and I have known\Neach other for twenty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.87,0:19:09.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She gets herself torn up like she\Nis now and ends up at my door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.95,0:19:14.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since we were children,\Nit's been one fight after another...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.15,0:19:16.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and I'd tend to\Nher injuries every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.12,0:19:20.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's a woman, but her body's\Ncovered in a patchwork of scars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.32,0:19:25.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And thanks to that, I must say\NI'm adept at stitching up wounds now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:28.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and I've picked up quite a bit\Nabout medicinal herbs too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:35.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Has Balsa been a bodyguard\Never since she was a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.81,0:19:41.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. When we were small,\Nshe trained from sunup to sundown.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.81,0:19:46.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was about six years ago that she\Nstarted working as a bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.02,0:19:50.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Has it already been that long?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.42,0:19:54.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, Balsa saved\Nmy life and Saya's too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.96,0:20:01.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're both orphans, so there aren't\Nany adults who look out for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.70,0:20:08.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've raised Saya as my sister,\Nbut then slave traders tried to take her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.97,0:20:13.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's when Balsa\Nshowed up and saved the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.68,0:20:15.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Without even taking off\Nthe sheath of her spear...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.61,0:20:17.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...she dispatched all six of them\Nin the blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.85,0:20:21.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really... She's a\Npowerful lady, this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.75,0:20:25.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's put that strength to good use,\Nsaving countless people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.95,0:20:29.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And in the process,\NI've also taken lots of lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.06,0:20:32.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're awake, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.76,0:20:34.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.23,0:20:38.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really. I'm aching all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:41.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll be better soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.61,0:20:49.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to change your\Nbandages and salves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.06,0:21:12.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really, you heal amazingly\Nquickly for a middle-aged lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.90,0:21:14.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will I be up and around\Nsooner than you thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.97,0:21:16.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.37,0:21:18.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the wound is closed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.14,0:21:22.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the cut flesh and muscle\Nwon't be good as new right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.08,0:21:29.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I remember this scar!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.58,0:21:32.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the very first cut\Nthat I ever stitched.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.29,0:21:35.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, you were crying\Nyour eyes out at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.09,0:21:36.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.49,0:21:38.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it. That tickles!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.60,0:21:41.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.23,0:21:44.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Something strange is\Nhappening to my stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.87,0:21:46.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.11,0:21:57.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen such a prince!\NYou couldn't even tell you were hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.91,0:22:01.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is what hunger feels like?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.49,0:22:10.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.06,0:22:13.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This tastes far better than\Nanything I ate at the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.83,0:22:15.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.80,0:22:21.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.60,0:22:24.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An egg... An egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.57,0:22:25.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress Torogai!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.44,0:22:27.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.68,0:22:33.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An egg... An egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.08,0:22:35.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.05,0:22:39.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.57,0:22:52.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.84,0:23:04.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The egg!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.05,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.51,0:24:45.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That which resides within Chagum\Nis the egg of a spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.08,0:24:48.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To unravel its mysteries, the door\Nto the Chamber of the Epistles opens.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.12,0:24:52.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time,\N"Secret Plan, The Blue Hand."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 5\NSecret Plan, The Blue Hand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.55,0:24:55.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, can you break\Nthe net that encircles you?
